          	<a href="http://www.pewforum.org/2015/01/05/faith-on-the-hill/"><img src="http://www.pewforum.org/files/2015/01/PF_15.01.05_ReligionCongress_HP.png" width="260" height="260"></a>
				
			<div class="post">
			  <p class="meta"><span class="project religion">polling and analysis</span><span class="date left-seperator">Jan 5, 2015</span></p>
			  <h1><a href="http://www.pewforum.org/2015/01/05/faith-on-the-hill/">Faith on the Hill</a></h1>
              			  <div class="blurb">
			  	<p>More than nine-in-ten members of the newly elected 114th Congress are Christian &#8212; a significantly higher share than is seen in the general population. However, many other major religious groups are represented in the body, including Jews, Buddhists, Muslims, Hindus and the unaffiliated.</p>
